n in constituency No. 1 (East Prussia)\n* [[Franz Feldmann]] (1868\u20131937)\n* [[Gustav Ferl]] (1890\u20131970)\n* [[Hermann Fleissner]] (1865\u20131939)\n* [[August Fr\u00f6lich]] (Th\u00fcringen) (1877\u20131966)\n* [[Otto Geiselhart]] entered Reichstag on 26 February 1929 for Abg. Saenger\n* [[Paul Gerlach]]\n* [[Emil Girbig]]\n* [[Georg Graf (Politiker)|Georg Graf]] (1881\u20131952)\n* [[Peter Gra\u00dfmann]] (1873\u20131939)\n* [[Georg Graupe]] (Zwickau) (1875\u20131959) entered Reichstag on 15 February 1930 for Abg. Dr. Levi\n* [[Otto Grotewohl]] (1894\u20131964)\n* [[Ernst Heilmann]] (Frankfurt) (1881\u20131940)\n* [[Hugo Heimann]] (Berlin) (1859\u20131951)\n* [[Kurt Heinig]] (1886\u20131956)\n* [[Alfred Henke]]\n* [[Karl Hermann (SPD)|Karl Hermann]] (1885\u20131973) left Reichstag on 12 May 1930\n* [[Paul Hertz|Dr. Paul Hertz]] (1888\u20131961)\n* [[Karl Hildenbrand]] (W\u00fcrttemberg) (1864\u20131935)\n* [[Rudolf Hilferding|Dr. Rudolf Hilferding]] (1877\u20131941)\n* [[Johannes Hoffmann (SPD)|Johannes Hoffmann]] (Kaiserslautern) (1867\u20131930)\n* [[Oskar H\u00fcnlich]] (1887\u20131963)\n* [[Friedrich Ernst Husemann]] (1873\u20131935)\n* [[Carl J\u00e4cker]]\n* [[Gerhard Jacobshagen]]\n* [[Alfred Janschek]] (1874\u20131955)\n* [[Marie Juchacz]] (1879\u20131956)\n* [[Paul Junke]]\n* [[August Karsten]] (1888-??)\n* [[Wilhelm Keil]] (1870\u20131968)\n* [[Franz Kotzke]]\n* [[Hermann Kr\u00e4tzig]] (1871\u20131954)\n* [[Wilhelm Kr\u00f6ger]] (Rostock)\n* [[Richard Kr\u00fcger]] (Merseburg) left Reichstag on 22 June 1929\n* [[Bernhard Kuhnt]] (1876\u20131946)\n* [[Marie Kunert]]\n* [[Franz K\u00fcnstler]] (1888\u20131942)\n* [[Nanny Kurf\u00fcrst]], [[Social Democratic Party of Germany|SPD]]\n* [[Otto Landsberg]] (1869\u20131957)\n* [[Julius Leber|Dr. Julius Leber]] (1891\u20131945)\n* [[Paul Levi|Dr. Paul Levi]] (1883\u20131930) died on 9 February 1930\n* [[Heinrich Wilhelm Limbertz]]\n* [[Richard Lipinski]] (1867\u20131936)\n* [[Carl Litke]] (1897\u20131962)\n* [[Paul L\u00f6be]] (1875\u20131967)\n* [[Kurt L\u00f6wenstein|Dr. Kurt L\u00f6wenstein]] (1895\u20131939)\n* [[Josef L\u00fcbbring]]\n* [[Konrad Ludwig]]\n* [[Werner Lufft]]\n* [[Karl Mache]]\n* [[Ludwig Marum]] (1882\u20131934)\n* [[Stefan Meier]] (Baden)\n* [[Arthur Mertins]] (1898\u20131979) entered Reichstag on 28 August 1929 for Abg. Schulz (K\u00f6nigsberg)\n* [[Franz Metz]]\n* [[Oscar Meyer]] (Berlin)\n* [[Julius Moses|Dr. Julius Moses]] (1868\u20131942)\n* [[Hermann M\u00fcller (politician)|Hermann M\u00fcller]] (Franken) (1876\u20131931)\n* [[Anna Nemitz]] (1873\u20131962)\n* [[Friedrich Nowack]] (1890\u20131959)\n* [[Toni Pf\u00fclf|Antonie Pf\u00fclf]] (1877\u20131933)\n* [[Otto Friedrich Passehl]] (Pommern),\n* [[Friedrich Peine]]\n* [[Franz Peters (Politiker)|Franz Peters]] (1888-??)\n* [[Heinrich Peus]]\n* [[Friedrich Puchta]] (1883\u20131945)\n* [[Ludwig Quessel|Dr. Ludwig Quessel]]\n* [[Johanna Reitze]] (1878\u20131949)\n* [[Adam Remmele]] (Baden) (1877\u20131951)\n* [[Heinrich Richter]] (Hildesheim)\n* [[Max Richter]] (Schleswig-Holstein)\n* [[Kurt Rosenfeld|Dr. Kurt Rosenfeld]] (1877\u20131943)\n* [[Erich Ro\u00dfmann]] (W\u00fcrttemberg) (1884\u20131953)\n* [[Alwin Saenger]] died on 18 February 1929\n* [[Hugo Saupe]] (Leipzig) (1883-??)\n* [[Joseph Schaffner]]\n* [[Franz Scheffel]]\n* [[Philipp Scheidemann]] (1865\u20131939)\n* [[Luise Schiffgens]]\n* [[Richard Schiller]]\n* [[Johannes Schirmer]] (Dresden)\n* [[Alexander Schlicke]] (1863\u20131940)\n* [[Wilhelm Schl\u00fcter]] died am 8 January 1930\n* [[Robert Schmidt (German politician)|Robert Schmidt]] (Berlin) (1864\u20131943)\n* [[Georg Schmidt (politician)|Georg Schmidt]] (C\u00f6penick) (1875\u20131946)\n* [[Richard Schmidt (Sachsen)|Richard Schmidt]] (Mei\u00dfen) (1871\u20131945)\n* [[Georg Sch\u00f6pflin]]\n* [[Carl Schreck]] (Bielefeld) (1873\u20131956)\n* [[Adele Schreiber-Krieger]]\n* [[Louise Schroeder]] (Schleswig-Holstein) (1887\u20131957)\n* [[Hermann Schulz (Politiker)|Hermann Schulz]] (K\u00f6nigsberg) died on 20 August 1929\n* [[Berta Schulz]] (Westfalen)\n* [[Oswald Schumann]] (Frankfurt)\n* [[Gustav Schumann]] (Stettin)\n* [[Hans Seidel (Politiker)|Hans Seidel]]\n* [[Toni Sender|Tony Sender]] (1888\u20131964)\n* [[Max Seppel]]\n* [[Carl Severing]] (1875\u20131952)\n* [[Max Seydewitz]] (1892\u20131987)\n* [[Anna Siemsen|Dr. Anna Siemsen]] (1882\u20131951)\n* [[August Siemsen|Dr. August Siemsen]] (Th\u00fcringen) (1884\u20131958) entered Reichstag on 17 May 1930 for Abg. Hermann\n* [[Josef Simon (Politiker)|Josef Simon]] (Franken)\n* [[Georg Simon]] (Schwaben)\n* [[Wilhelm Sollmann]] (1881\u20131951)\n* [[Heinrich Schulz]] (Bremen) (1872\u20131932)\n* [[Karl Spiegel]]\n* [[Wilhelm Staab]]\n* [[Friedrich Stampfer]] (1874\u20131957)\n* [[Anna Stegmann|Dr. Anna Stegmann]]\n* [[Willy Steinkopf]] (1885\u20131953)\n* [[Johannes Stelling]] (1877\u20131933)\n* [[Heinrich Str\u00f6bel]] (1869\u20131944)\n* [[Daniel St\u00fccklen]] (1869\u20131945)\n* [[Fritz Tarnow]] (1880\u20131951)\n* [[Paul Taubadel]] (1875\u20131937)\n* [[Hermann Tempel]]\n* [[Johannes Thabor]]\n* [[Carl Ulrich]] (Hessen) (1853\u20131933)\n* [[Hans Unterleitner]] (1890\u20131971)\n* [[Hans Vogel|Johann Vogel]] (1881\u20131945)\n* [[Klara Weich]]\n* [[Otto Wels]] (1872\u20131939)\n* [[Carl Wendemuth]]\n* [[Georg Wendt]]\n* [[Rudolf Wissell]] (1869\u20131962)\n* [[Otto Witte]]\n* [[Mathilde Wurm]] (1874\u20131935)\n* [[Hermann M\u00fcller (Lichtenberg)|Hermann M\u00fcller]] ([[Lichtenberg]]) (1868\u20131932\n* [[Michael Schnabrich]] (1880\u20131939)\n\n==[[German National People's Party]]==\nIn German ''Deutschnationale Volkspartei'', DNVP.\n\n* [[Dirk Agena|Dr. Dirk Agena]]\n* [[Paul Bang|Dr. Paul Bang]]\n* [[Gustav von Bartenwerffer]], [[DNVP]], entered Reichstag 4 April 1930 for Abg. Schiele\n* [[Georg Bachmann]], [[DNVP]]\n* [[Wilhelm Bazille]] (1874\u20131934), [[DNVP]]\n* [[Emil Berndt]], [[DNVP]]\n* [[Franz Biener]] (1866\u20131940), [[DNVP]]\n* [[Wilhelm Bruhn]] (1869\u20131951), [[DNVP]], left the party October 1929 and became an independent member\n* [[Wilhelm Dingler]], [[DNVP]]\n* [[Alwin Domsch]] (Dresden), [[DNVP]]\n* [[Gottfried von Dryander|Dr. Gottfried von Dryander]], [[DNVP]]\n* [[Botho-Wendt Graf zu Eulenburg]], [[DNVP]]\n* [[Friedrich Everling|Dr. Friedrich Everling]], [[DNVP]]\n* [[Axel Freiherr von Freytag-Loringhoven|Dr. Axel Freiherr von Freytag-Loringhoven]], [[DNVP]]\n* [[Curt Wilhelm Fromm]], [[DNVP]]\n* [[Heinrich Gerns]] (1892\u20131963), [[DNVP]]\n* [[Georg Gottheiner]], [[DNVP]]\n* [[Walther Graef]] (Th\u00fcringen), [[DNVP]]\n* [[Gottfried Gok]], [[DNVP]]\n* [[Hans von Goldacker]], [[DNVP]]\n* [[Heinrich Haag]], [[DNVP]]\n* [[Robert Hampe]], [[DNVP]]\n* [[Alfred Hanemann|Dr. Alfred Hanemann]], [[DNVP]]\n* [[Georg Hartmann (Politiker)|Georg Hartmann]], [[DNVP]]\n* [[Johann Jacob Ha\u00dflacher|Dr. Johann Jacob Ha\u00dflacher]], [[DNVP]]\n* [[Oskar Hergt]] (1869\u20131967), [[DNVP]]\n* [[Alfred Hugenberg|Dr. Alfred Hugenberg]] (1865\u20131951), [[DNVP]]\n* [[Emil Hemeter]], [[DNVP]]\n* [[Willy Jandrey]] (1877\u20131945), [[DNVP]]\n* [[Fritz Kleiner|Dr. Fritz Kleiner]], [[DNVP]], entered Reichstag 2 December 1929 for Abg. Wolf (Oppeln)\n* [[Wilhelm Koch]] (D\u00fcsseldorf), [[DNVP]]\n* [[Albrecht Philipp|Dr. Albrecht Philipp]] (1883\u20131962), [[DNVP]]\n* [[Dietrich Preyer|Dr. Dr. Dietrich Preyer]], [[DNVP]]\n* [[Wilhelm Vogt]] (W\u00fcrttemberg), [[DNVP]]\n* [[Max Wallraf]], [[DNVP]]\n* [[Kurt Wege (DNVP)|Kurt Wege]], [[DNVP]]\n* [[Kuno von Westarp|Kuno Graf von Westarp]] (1864\u20131945)\n* [[Erich Wienbeck|Dr. Erich Wienbeck]]\n* [[Edgar Wolf]] (Oppeln) resigned 30 November 1929\n* [[Johannes Wolf]] (Stettin)\n* [[Ernst Oberfohren|Dr. Ernst Oberfohren]] (1881\u20131933), [[DNVP]] - party chairman from 12 December 1929 \n* [[Wilhelm Ohler]]\n* [[Reinhold Quaatz|Dr. Reinhold Quaatz]]\n* [[Hans von Troilo]]\n* [[Walther Rademacher|Dr. Walther Rademacher]]\n* [[Jakob Reichert|Dr. Jakob Reichert]]\n* [[Praetorius Freiherr von Richthofen]]\n* [[Carl Rieseberg]]\n* [[Hans Sachs (Reichstagsabgeordneter)|Hans Sachs]] (1874\u20131947), National Liberal Land Party, Guest of the DNVP\n* [[Walter Stubbendorff]]\n* [[Hermann Strathmann|D. Hermann Strathmann]]\n* [[Martin Schiele]] (1870\u20131939), [[DNVP]], resigned 31 March 1930\n* [[Karl Steiniger|Dr. Karl Steiniger]]\n* [[Hermann Staffehl]] (Potsdam)\n* [[Otto Schmidt-Hannover|Otto Schmidt]] (Hannover) (1888\u20131971)\n* [[Otto Schmidt (Stettin)|Otto Schmidt]] (Stettin)\n* [[Hermann Schr\u00f6ter]] (Liegnitz)\n* [[Georg Schultz]] (Bromberg) (1860\u20131945)\n* [[Max Soth]]\n* [[Martin Spahn|Dr. Martin Spahn]] (1875\u20131945)\n* [[Ernst Mentzel]]\n* [[Paula M\u00fcller-Otfried]] (1865\u20131946)\n* [[Wilhelm Laverrenz]] (1879\u20131955)\n* [[Annagrete Lehmann]]\n* [[Bernhard Leopold]]\n* [[Paul von Lettow-Vorbeck]] (1870\u20131964)\n* [[Heinrich Lind]] later independent\n\n===Later formed CNAG===\nThese DNVP members later merged with CNBL to form the Christian National Labor Society (''Christlich-Nationale Arbeitsgemeinschaft'', CNAG).\n\n* [[Emil Hartwig]] (Berlin)\n* [[Otto Hoetzsch|Dr. Otto Hoetzsch]] (1876\u20131946)\n* [[Gottfried Treviranus]] (1891\u20131971)\n* [[Franz Behrens]] (1872\u20131943)\n* [[Gustav H\u00fclser]]\n* [[Wilhelm M\u00f6nke]]\n* [[Reinhard Mumm|D. Reinhard Mumm]] (1873\u20131932)\n* [[Walter von Keudell]] (1884\u20131973)\n* [[Moritz Kl\u00f6nne]]\n* [[Walther Lambach]]\n* [[Paul Lejeune-Jung|Dr. Paul Lejeune-Jung]] (1882\u20131944)\n* [[Hans Erdmann von Lindeiner-Wildau]]\n* [[Hans Schlange-Sch\u00f6ningen|Hans Schlange]] (1886\u20131960)\n\n==[[Centre Party (Germany)]]==\nIn German ''Zentrum''.\n* Josef Andre left Reichstag on 31 October 1928\n* [[Adalbert Beck]] (Oppeln)\n* {{ill|Johannes Becker (politician, born 1875)|lt=Johannes Becker|de|Johannes Becker (Politiker)}} (Arnsberg) (1875\u20131955)\n* [[Johannes Bell|Dr. Johannes Bell]] (1868\u20131949)\n* [[Franz Bielefeld]]\n* [[Johannes Blum]] (Krefeld) (1857\u20131946)\n* [[Fritz Bockius|Dr. Fritz Bockius]]\n* [[Eugen Bolz]] (1881\u20131945)\n* [[Franz Bornefeld-Ettmann]]\n* [[Heinrich Brauns|Dr. Heinrich Brauns]] (K\u00f6ln) (1868\u20131939)\n* [[Heinrich Br\u00fcning|Dr. Heinrich Br\u00fcning]] (1885\u20131970)\n* [[August Crone-M\u00fcnzebrock|Dr. August Crone-M\u00fcnzebrock]]\n* [[Anton Damm]]\n* [[Friedrich Dessauer|Dr. Friedrich Dessauer]] (1881\u20131963)\n* Carl Diez (1877\u20131969)\n* [[Johannes Drees|Dr. Johannes Drees]]\n* Franz Ehrhardt (1880\u20131956)\n* Joseph Ersing (1882\u20131956)\n* [[Thomas Esser]]\n* [[Heinrich Fahrenbach]]\n* [[Franz Feilmayr]]\n* [[Ernst F\u00f6hr|Dr. Ernst F\u00f6hr]] (Baden)\n* [[Hedwig Fuchs]] entered Reichstag on  8 March 1929 for Lammers\n* [[Otto Gerig]]\n* [[Johannes Giesberts]] (1865\u20131938)\n* [[Johannes Gro\u00df (Politiker)|Johannes Gro\u00df]] entered Reichstag on 7 November 1928 for Andre\n* [[Theodor von Gu\u00e9rard]] (1863\u20131943)\n* [[Heinrich Hartwig]] (Oppeln)\n* [[Andreas Hermes|Dr. Andreas Hermes]] (1878\u20131964)\n* [[Carl Herold]]\n* [[Hermann Hofmann]] (Ludwigshafen)\n* [[Heinrich Imbusch]] (1878\u20131945)\n* [[Josef Joos]] (1878\u20131965)\n* [[Ludwig Kaas|Dr. Ludwig Kaas]] (Trier) (1881\u20131952)\n* [[Peter Kerp]]\n* [[Florian Kl\u00f6ckner]]\n* [[Heinrich K\u00f6hler|Dr. Heinrich K\u00f6hler]] (1878\u20131949)\n* [[Clemens Lammers]] left Reichstag on 1 March 1929\n* [[Wilhelm Marx]] (1863\u20131946)\n* [[Georg Nauheim]]\n* [[Agnes Neuhaus]] (1854\u20131944)\n* [[Hugo Neumann]]\n* [[Matthias Neyses]]\n* [[Hans Nientimp]] later independent\n* [[Ludwig Perlitius|Dr. Ludwig Perlitius]]\n* [[Franz Riesener]]\n* [[Adam Stegerwald]] (1874\u20131945)\n* [[Richard Sch\u00f6nborn]]\n* [[Paul Schulz-Gahmen]]\n* [[Georg Schreiber|D. Dr. Georg Schreiber]] (1882\u20131963)\n* [[Josef Sinn]] resigned 11 April 1929\n* [[Jean-Albert Schwarz]] (Frankfurt) (1873\u20131957)\n* [[Rudolf Schetter|Dr. Rudolf Schetter]] (K\u00f6ln) entered Reich