l Papke]]\n* [[Nikolaus Pfaff]], [[Communist Party of Germany|KPD]], entered Reichstag on 24 August 1929 for H\u00f6llein\n* [[Hans Pfeiffer (Politiker)|Hans Pfeiffer]] (1895\u20131968)\n* [[Wilhelm Pieck]] (1876\u20131960)\n* [[Ernst Putz]] (1896\u20131933\n* [[Siegfried R\u00e4del]] (1893\u20131943)\n* [[Paul Redlich]]\n* [[Maria Reese]] (1889\u20131958), [[Social Democratic Party of Germany|SPD]], in November 1929 alternate of the [[Communist Party of Germany|KPD]]\n* [[Hermann Remmele]] (Berlin) (1880\u20131939)\n* [[Wilhelm Repschl\u00e4ger]] (1870\u20131945), [[Communist Party of Germany|KPD]]\n* [[Heinrich Schmitt]] (Merseburg) (1895\u20131951)\n* [[Ernst Schneller]] (1890\u20131944)\n* [[Paul Schreck]] (Baden) (1892\u20131948)\n* [[Walter Stoecker]] (1891\u20131931), [[Communist Party of Germany|KPD]], floor leader from 1929\n* [[Max Str\u00f6tzel]] (1885\u20131945)\n* [[Ernst Th\u00e4lmann]] (1886\u20131944)\n* [[Matthias Thesen]] (1891\u20131944)\n* [[Ernst Torgler]] (1893\u20131963), [[Communist Party of Germany|KPD]] - floor leader to 1929\n* [[Walter Ulbricht]] (Westfalen) (1893\u20131973)\n* [[Artur Vogt]] (Westfalen) (1894\u20131964)\n* [[Clara Zetkin]] (1857\u20131933)\n* [[Hans Kippenberger]] (1898\u20131937)\n* [[Hans Kollwitz]] (1893\u20131948)\n* [[Wilhelm Koenen]] (1886\u20131963)\n\n==[[German People's Party]]==\n* [[Helmuth Albrecht]]\n* [[Michael Bayersd\u00f6rfer|Dr. Michael Bayersd\u00f6rfer]], [[Bayerische Volkspartei|BVP]]\n* [[Johann Becker (politician)|Johann Becker]] (Hessen) (1869\u20131951)\n* [[Heinrich Beythien]]\n* [[Theodor Bickes]]\n* [[Franz Br\u00fcninghaus]]\n* [[Friedrich Cramm]]\n* [[Carl Cremer|Dr. Carl Cremer]]\n* [[Julius Curtius|Dr. Julius Curtius]] (1877\u20131948)\n* [[Walther Dauch]] (Hamburg)\n* [[Eduard Dingeldey]] (1886\u20131942)\n* [[Adolf Findeisen]]\n* [[Erich von Gilsa]]\n* [[Christian G\u00fcnther]]\n* [[Heinrich Janson]]\n* [[Friedrich Pfeffer|Dr. Friedrich Pfeffer]]\n* [[Albert Zapf|Dr. Albert Zapf]]\n* [[